10/07/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer reaffirmed on Friday (7 July) that the Alliance would keep its troops in Kosovo, suggesting that no changes in the current troop strength of 17,000 are being considered for now.
His comment came during a visit to Athens, last stop on a tour of the region.
According to de Hoop Scheffer, "NATO cannot afford to lower its guard" in Kosovo.
(Kathimerini - 08/07/06;
AFP, Xinhua - 07/07/06)
